formal_statement:
$$
\| \mathbb{E}[\mathbf{d}(\mathcal{S}_1)] - \mathbb{E}[\mathbf{d}(\mathcal{S}_2)] \|_2^2 = \underbrace{\sum_{i \in \mathcal{A}_{\text{stable}}} |\mathbb{E}[d_i(\mathcal{S}_1)] - \mathbb{E}[d_i(\mathcal{S}_2)]|^2}_{\text{Error from Stable Walkers}} + \underbrace{\sum_{i \in \mathcal{A}_{\text{unstable}}} |\mathbb{E}[d_i(\mathcal{S}_1)] - \mathbb{E}[d_i(\mathcal{S}_2)]|^2}_{\text{Error from Unstable Walkers}}
$$
